criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. patients with non-alcoholic fatty liver, fatty liver hepatitis and fatty liver
             fibrosis: all meet the diagnostic criteria of China's "Guidelines for the Prevention
             and Treatment of Non-alcoholic Fatty Liver Diseases (2018 Update)";

          2. Age between 18 and over 75;

          3. patient were never treated with no hormones and / or immunosuppressants and other
             liver protection drugs.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. combined with hepatitis virus infection;

          2. autoimmune liver disease;

          3. HIV infection;

          4. long-term alcohol abuse and / or other liver damage drugs;

          5. mental illness;

          6. Evidence of liver tumors (liver cancer or AFP > 100 ng/ml);

          7. decompensated cirrhosis;

          8. Serious diseases such as heart, brain, lung, kidney, etc. can not participate in
             long-term follow-up.
